# Example local env file for development. Copy this to `.env.local` and fill values.
# `.env.local` is ignored by git (see `.gitignore`) so it's safe to store secrets there for local dev.

# Required: Azure OpenAI key for the ChatGPT 5 Mini deployment. Keep this secret.
GPT_API_KEY="your-azure-openai-key"

# Optional overrides for Azure OpenAI configuration
#GPT_API_ENDPOINT="https://your-endpoint.openai.azure.com"
#GPT_DEPLOYMENT="gpt-5-mini"
#GPT_API_VERSION="2025-01-01-preview"

# Example DB connection string (optional for demo data)
#DATABASE_URL="mysql://root:mysecretpassword@localhost:3306/local"

# Notes:
# - Create a file named `.env.local` in the repo root with real values.
# - Restart the dev server after changing environment variables.
# - On CI (GitHub Actions) store GPT_API_KEY as a secret and inject it into the job environment.
